- I'm a boy.
- [chitters]

730
00:48:27.424 --> 00:48:30.844
I tried to tell you. I'm a boy.

731
00:48:30.885 --> 00:48:32.804
A human boy.

732
00:48:32.846 --> 00:48:35.056
- [sniffles]
- Oh...

733
00:48:35.098 --> 00:48:37.767
If you could only understand.

734
00:48:37.809 --> 00:48:44.023
[weeping]

735
00:48:47.235 --> 00:48:52.282
Ah... You know, lad,
that love business is a powerful thing.

736
00:48:52.615 --> 00:48:55.827
[sniffles, moans]

737
00:48:55.869 --> 00:48:58.163
Greater than gravity?

738
00:48:58.246 --> 00:49:00.999
Well, yes, boy, in its way.

739
00:49:01.040 --> 00:49:05.795
I'd... Yes, I'd say it's
the greatest force on earth.

740
00:49:06.713 --> 00:49:09.257
[sobbing]

741
00:49:14.179 --> 00:49:16.723
[woman screams]

742
00:49:18.057 --> 00:49:20.185
Ector! Ector!

743
00:49:20.226 --> 00:49:22.687
Sir Ector, the kitchen!

744
00:49:22.729 --> 00:49:24.230
Hold it, son.

745
00:49:24.272 --> 00:49:27.567
- [woman] Madness all over the place.
- Kay!

746
00:49:27.609 --> 00:49:29.068
Hold that, I say.

747
00:49:29.402 --> 00:49:31.529
[shouts]

748
00:49:34.991 --> 00:49:38.119
Now, what's all the commotion?

749
00:49:38.161 --> 00:49:41.039
Oh, the kitchen,
it's under an evil spell.

750
00:49:41.081 --> 00:49:42.916
- Huh?
- [woman] It's bewitched.

751
00:49:42.957 --> 00:49:45.919
No! I bet it's that old goat, Marvin.

752
00:49:45.960 --> 00:49:48.630
Come on, son.
I knew he'd give us trouble.

753
00:49:54.177 --> 00:49:55.845
Gadzooks!

754
00:49:57.472 --> 00:49:59.516
Black magic of the worst kind!

755
00:49:59.557 --> 00:50:02.102
Come on, Kay, to the attack!

756
00:50:02.143 --> 00:50:04.104
[groans]

757
00:50:20.370 --> 00:50:22.414
Heaven preserve us!

758
00:50:23.748 --> 00:50:25.041
Kay!

759
00:50:44.519 --> 00:50:48.440
- Now, what have we here?
- Jumpin' hop toads.

760
00:50:48.481 --> 00:50:51.192
Alakazam!

761
00:50:52.110 --> 00:50:53.945
[crashing]

762
00:50:56.364 --> 00:50:58.658
So there you are, you old goat.

763
00:51:00.702 --> 00:51:05.039
What's the idea of flinging
your evil spells all over the place?

764
00:51:05.081 --> 00:51:07.000
Oh, lend me a hand, boy.

765
00:51:12.213 --> 00:51:15.341
Well, what have you got
to say for yourself? Hmm?

766
00:51:15.383 --> 00:51:20.263
You call washing dishes
and sweeping floors a work of evil?

767
00:51:20.346 --> 00:51:24.184
I'll decide what's right and wrong
around here.

768
00:51:24.225 --> 00:51:27.270
Besides, that's the Wart's job,
one of his duties.

769
00:51:27.312 --> 00:51:28.521
Look here, boy.

770
00:51:28.563 --> 00:51:32.150
If you want to make that trip to London,
you'd better toe the mark.

771
00:51:32.233 --> 00:51:33.693
You old goat!

772
00:51:33.735 --> 00:51:37.155
If I ever catch you
in my kitchen again, I'll...

773
00:51:37.197 --> 00:51:40.200
Madam, you won't.

774
00:51:41.242 --> 00:51:42.619
Oh, dear.

775
00:51:42.660 --> 00:51:44.496
He's gone.

776
00:51:44.537 --> 00:51:46.372
Well, by Jove.

777
00:51:46.414 --> 00:51:49.501
We ought to run the old geezer
right out of the castle.

778
00:51:49.542 --> 00:51:52.212
Oh, no. No, no, Kay, no.

779
00:51:52.253 --> 00:51:55.006
He might cast an evil spell
on the lot of us.

780
00:51:55.048 --> 00:51:57.258
Turn us all into stone. Shh.

781
00:51:57.342 --> 00:52:00.428
No, there's no telling
what the old devil might do.

782
00:52:00.470 --> 00:52:02.347
He's not an old devil!

783
00:52:02.388 --> 00:52:06.434
He... he's good
and his magic is good, too.

784
00:52:06.476 --> 00:52:09.979
- If... If you just leave him alone.
- Now, look here, Wart.

785
00:52:10.021 --> 00:52:13.316
- That's three more demerits.
- Box his ears, Dad.

786
00:52:13.358 --> 00:52:18.071
Just because you can't understand
something, it doesn't mean it's wrong.

787
00:52:18.154 --> 00:52:19.405
Ten more demerits!

788
00:52:19.447 --> 00:52:22.742
You make all the rules and nobody else
can say anything.

789
00:52:22.784 --> 00:52:24.577
You've said a-plenty, boy.

790
00:52:24.619 --> 00:52:27.664
All that popping off
just cooked your goose. Kay!

791
00:52:27.705 --> 00:52:30.333
From now on,
young Hobbs is your squire.

792
00:52:30.375 --> 00:52:32.210
Did you hear that, Wart?

793
00:52:32.252 --> 00:52:36.214
Hobbs is going to be Kay's squire.

794
00:52:36.214 --> 00:52:37.382
Y... Yes, sir.

795
00:52:37.424 --> 00:52:41.261
That will teach you to pop off,
you little pipsqueak.

796
00:52:54.315 --> 00:52:56.192
I'm sorry, lad.

797
00:52:56.234 --> 00:52:59.028
I'm sorry. I spoiled everything.

798
00:52:59.070 --> 00:53:02.615
I know that trip to London
means a great deal to you.

799
00:53:02.657 --> 00:53:04.868
Oh, it's not your fault.

800
00:53:04.951 --> 00:53:06.870
I shouldn't have popped off.

801
00:53:06.911 --> 00:53:09.122
Now I'm really done for.

802
00:53:09.164 --> 00:53:11.791
No, no, you're in a great spot, boy.

803
00:53:11.833 --> 00:53:15.128
You can't go down now.
It can only be up from here.

804
00:53:15.170 --> 00:53:17.130
I'd like to know how.

805
00:53:17.213 --> 00:53:18.631
Use your head.

806
00:53:18.673 --> 00:53:20.592
An education, lad.

807
00:53:21.718 --> 00:53:26.139
- What good will that do?
- Get it first, then, who knows?

808
00:53:26.181 --> 00:53:27.807
Are you willing to try?

809
00:53:27.849 --> 00:53:31.227
[inhales] Well, what have I got to lose?

810
00:53:31.269 --> 00:53:33.938
That's the spirit.
We'll start tomorrow.

811
00:53:33.980 --> 00:53:36.399
We'll show 'em, won't we, boy?

812
00:53:36.441 --> 00:53:38.234
We sure will.

813
00:53:40.028 --> 00:53:42.614
[Merlin] Now, first of all, lad,

814
00:53:42.655 --> 00:53:46.117
we've got to get all of these
medieval ideas out of your head.

815
00:53:46.159 --> 00:53:49.079
Clear the way for new ideas.

816
00:53:49.120 --> 00:53:54.250
Knowledge of man's fabulous discoveries
in the centuries ahead.

817
00:53:54.334 --> 00:53:56.544
Now, that will be a great advantage.

818
00:53:56.628 --> 00:53:58.546
Advantage, indeed!

819
00:53:58.588 --> 00:54:02.592
If the boy says the world is round
they'll take him for a lunatic.

820
00:54:02.634 --> 00:54:05.637
- The world is round?
- Yes, yes, that's right.

821
00:54:05.678 --> 00:54:09.182
And it also goes around.

822
00:54:12.102 --> 00:54:15.939
- You mean, it'll be round someday?
- No, no, no. It's round now.

823
00:54:15.980 --> 00:54:18.858
Man will discover this
in centuries to come.

824
00:54:18.900 --> 00:54:20.527
And he will also find

825
00:54:20.568 --> 00:54:25.782
that the world is merely a tiny speck
in the universe.

826
00:54:25.824 --> 00:54:29.035
- Universe?
- Ah. You're only confusing the boy.

827
00:54:29.077 --> 00:54:33.164
He'll be so mixed up he'll...
he'll be wearing his shoes on his head.

828
00:54:33.206 --> 00:54:35.333
Man has always learned from the past.

829
00:54:35.375 --> 00:54:38.211
After all, you can't learn history
in reverse.

830
00:54:38.253 --> 00:54:41.005
It's confusing enough,
for heaven's sakes.

831
00:54:41.047 --> 00:54:43.800
- All right. All right.
- [coughing]

832
00:54:43.842 --> 00:54:47.220
Have it your way, Archimedes.
You're in charge.

833
00:54:47.262 --> 00:54:49.139
You're the headmaster now.

834
00:54:49.180 --> 00:54:51.808
So, from now on he's your pupil.

835
00:54:53.351 --> 00:54:56.688
So, from now on, boy,

836
00:54:56.729 --> 00:54:58.481
you do as I say.

837
00:54:58.523 --> 00:55:00.358
- Yes, sir.
- All right.

838
00:55:00.400 --> 00:55:04.612
Now, to start off,
I want you to read these books.

839
00:55:05.155 --> 00:55:06.406
All of them?

840
00:55:06.448 --> 00:55:09.868
That, my boy,
is a mountain of knowledge.

841
00:55:09.909 --> 00:55:12.662
- But I can't read.
- What, what? What!

842
00:55:12.704 --> 00:55:15.874
- I don't suppose you know how to write?
- No, sir.

843
00:55:15.915 --> 00:55:18.710
- Well, what do you know?
- Well, I...

844
00:55:18.752 --> 00:55:22.714
Never mind, never mind.
We'll start at the bottom. The ABC's.

845
00:55:23.757 --> 00:55:27.594
First the A and now the B.

846
00:55:27.677 --> 00:55:31.389
Loop and around and there's the C.

847
00:55:31.431 --> 00:55:34.517
Merlin, look. I can write!

848
00:55:34.559 --> 00:55:37.145
Oh, yes, yes.
That's very good, boy.

849
00:55:37.187 --> 00:55:39.397
Hen scratch, that's all.
Hen scratch.

850
00:55:39.481 --> 00:55:42.817
Now, come on. D, E, F.

851
00:55:42.859 --> 00:55:45.153
And now the G.

852
00:55:45.195 --> 00:55:48.907
You see, it's as simple as...
No, no, no, no, boy!

853
00:55:48.948 --> 00:55:53.203
Use your head, use your head, will you?
How do you expect to learn anything?

854
00:55:53.203 --> 00:55:54.412
Archimedes.

855
00:55:54.454 --> 00:55:59.793
Have you seen that flying machine model?

856
00:55:59.834 --> 00:56:03.671
I have nothing to do with your
futuristic fiddle-faddle, you know that.

857
00:56:03.755 --> 00:56:06.674
- What's that thing up there?
- Hmm?

858
00:56:06.716 --> 00:56:09.719
Oh, yes, of course. Here we are.

859
00:56:09.761 --> 00:56:12.639
Do you mean man will fly
in one of those someday?

860
00:56:12.680 --> 00:56:16.601
If man were meant to fly,
he'd have been born with wings.

861
00:56:17.352 --> 00:56:22.482
I am about to prove otherwise,
Archimedes, if you care to watch.

862
00:56:23.316 --> 00:56:25.360
Here she goes!

863
00:56:26.736 --> 00:56:29.280
No, no, no!

864
00:56:31.366 --> 00:56:33.493
Man will fly, all right.

865
00:56:34.327 --> 00:56:36.121
Just like a rock.

866
00:56:36.162 --> 00:56:38.623
[Archimedes laughing]

867
00:56:38.706 --> 00:56:43.586
It would have worked if...
if it weren't for this infernal beard.

868
00:56:54.806 --> 00:56:56.516
I never...

869
00:56:56.558 --> 00:56:59.727
Never in my whole...

870
00:57:04.732 --> 00:57:08.319
Man will fly someday, I tell you.

871
00:57:08.403 --> 00:57:11.281
I have been there.
I have seen it.

872
00:57:11.322 --> 00:57:15.702
Oh, I do hope so.
I've always dreamed about flying.

873
00:57:15.744 --> 00:57:19.581
That I was a bird and that
I could go sailing all over the sky,

874
00:57:19.622 --> 00:57:21.541
high above everything.

875
00:57:21.583 --> 00:57:24.794
Avis alitus avita atheta.
Prestidigitonium.

876
00:57:24.836 --> 00:57:27.130
It's my favourite dream.

877
00:57:27.172 --> 00:57:30.717
Oh, but then, I suppose
everybody dreams about flying.

878
00:57:31.885 --> 00:57:34.345
I'm a bird, I'm a bird,
I'm a bird!

879
00:57:34.429 --> 00:57:37.724
Hold it, boy.
Not so fast, not so fast.

880
00:57:37.766 --> 00:57:41.895
First, I'd better explain the mechanics
of a bird's wing.

881
00:57:41.936 --> 00:57:45.482
Now, these large feathers

882
00:57:45.523 --> 00:57:48.943
are called the primaries, and...

883
00:57:48.985 --> 00:57:53.740
And since when do you know
all about birds' wings?

884
00:57:53.782 --> 00:57:57.619
I have made an extensive study
of birds in flight and I...

885
00:57:57.702 --> 00:58:01.748
And if you don't mind,
I happen to be a bird.

886
00:58:01.790 --> 00:58:05.960
All right, Mr Know-it-All!
He's your pupil.

887
00:58:06.002 --> 00:58:07.295
Ouch.

888
00:58:07.337 --> 00:58:12.467
Now, boy, flying is not merely
some crude mechanical process.

889
00:58:12.509 --> 00:58:14.636
[clearing throat]

890
00:58:14.677 --> 00:58:18.515
It is a delicate art,
purely aesthetic,

891
00:58:18.556 --> 00:58:20.475
poetry of motion.

892
00:58:20.517 --> 00:58:22.811
And the best way to learn it
is to do it.

893
00:58:22.894 --> 00:58:26.731
Now, since we're pretty far up,
we'll start with a glide.

894
00:58:26.815 --> 00:58:30.151
Spread your wings way out.
Way out!

895
00:58:30.193 --> 00:58:31.528
That's it, that's it.

896
00:58:31.569 --> 00:58:33.780
Now, fan your tail.

897
00:58:33.822 --> 00:58:37.742
Tippety toe, tippety toe
and off we go.

898
00:58:40.870 --> 00:58:43.081
Now, tuck your feet under like me.

899
00:58:43.123 --> 00:58:46.042
That's it. That's the idea.

900
00:58:47.419 --> 00:58:48.795
Whoa. What?

901
00:58:48.837 --> 00:58:52.215
And don't fight the air currents.
Use them.

902
00:59:03.643 --> 00:59:06.271
Why, say, boy!

903
00:59:06.312 --> 00:59:08.690
That's pretty good.

904
00:59:08.731 --> 00:59:11.651
Well, boy, you're a natural.

905
00:59:11.693 --> 00:59:15.238
Are you sure this is
the first time that you...

906
00:59:15.280 --> 00:59:17.949
Wart, Wart, hawk, hawk!

907
00:59:17.991 --> 00:59:21.536
Look out, boy, heads up!
Come on, Wart!

908
00:59:22.871 --> 00:59:24.831
Archimedes, help!

909
00:59:28.710 --> 00:59:29.961
[hawk screeching]

910
00:59:30.003 --> 00:59:34.048
[Archimedes] Wart! Wart!

911
00:59:39.053 --> 00:59:40.805
[panting]

912
00:59:44.934 --> 00:59:46.853
What? Oh!

913
00:59:49.189 --> 00:59:52.692
[coughing]

914
00:59:54.611 --> 00:59:56.571
Sounds like someone's sick.

915
00:59:56.613 --> 00:59:58.656
How lovely.

916
00:59:58.698 --> 01:00:00.909
I do hope it's serious.

917
01:00:00.992 --> 01:00:03.286
Something dreadful.

918
01:00:03.369 --> 01:00:07.540
Oh, bat gizzards. It's nothing
but a scrawny little sparrow

919
01:00:07.582 --> 01:00:09.417
with a beak full of soot.

920
01:00:09.459 --> 01:00:12.670
Oh, I'm not really a sparrow.
I'm a boy.

921
01:00:12.712 --> 01:00:14.506
A boy?

922
01:00:14.547 --> 01:00:18.760
Merlin changed me with his magic.
He's the world's most powerful wizard.

923
01:00:18.802 --> 01:00:20.178
Merlin!

924
01:00:20.970 --> 01:00:24.516
Merlin.
The world's most powerful bungler.

925
01:00:24.557 --> 01:00:27.602
Why, boy, I've got more magic
in one little finger.

926
01:00:29.312 --> 01:00:33.441
Now, don't tell me you've never heard
of the Marvellous Madam Mim?

927
01:00:33.483 --> 01:00:36.111
Well, no, I don't guess so.

928
01:00:36.152 --> 01:00:37.654
Madam Mim!

929
01:00:38.321 --> 01:00:39.697
Good heavens.

930
01:00:39.739 --> 01:00:41.783
Why, boy, I'm the greatest.

931
01:00:41.825 --> 01:00:44.119
I'm truly marvellous.

932
01:00:44.160 --> 01:00:48.873
<i>♪ With only a touch
I have the power ♪</i>

933
01:00:48.915 --> 01:00:50.500
<i>♪ Zim zabberim bim ♪</i>

934
01:00:50.542 --> 01:00:53.002
<i>♪ To wither a flower ♪</i>

935
01:00:53.086 --> 01:00:56.423
<i>♪ I find delight
in the gruesome and grim ♪</i>

936
01:00:56.506 --> 01:00:59.300
- Oh, that's terrible.
- Thank you, my boy.

937
01:00:59.342 --> 01:01:02.929
But that's nothing, nothing for me.

938
01:01:02.971 --> 01:01:07.934
<i>♪ Cos I'm the magnificent, marvellous,
mad Madam Mim ♪</i>

939
01:01:08.017 --> 01:01:11.688
You know what?
I can even change size.

940
01:01:11.729 --> 01:01:13.898
<i>♪ I can be huge ♪</i>

941
01:01:14.774 --> 01:01:17.235
<i>♪ Fill the whole house ♪</i>

942
01:01:17.277 --> 01:01:20.530
<i>♪ I can be teeny,
small as a mouse ♪</i>

943
01:01:20.572 --> 01:01:24.242
<i>♪ Black sorcery is my dish of tea ♪</i>

944
01:01:26.494 --> 01:01:28.204
<i>♪ It comes easy to me ♪</i>

945
01:01:28.246 --> 01:01:32.584
<i>♪ Cos I'm the magnificent, marvellous,
mad Madam Mim ♪</i>

946
01:01:32.625 --> 01:01:35.670
[cackling]

947
01:01:35.712 --> 01:01:38.882
Marvellous, boy.
Marvellous, I'm marvellous.

948
01:01:41.426 --> 01:01:45.680
Say, lad, did you know
that I can make myself uglier yet?

949
01:01:45.722 --> 01:01:48.141
That would be some trick.

950
01:01:48.892 --> 01:01:51.436
- I mean...
- Want to bet?

951
01:01:51.478 --> 01:01:53.688
- Boo!
- Oh!

952
01:01:53.730 --> 01:01:55.899
You see? I win, I win!

953
01:01:55.940 --> 01:01:58.401
Aren't I hideous, boy?

954
01:01:58.485 --> 01:02:02.030
- Perfectly revolting?
- Well, uh... Yes, ma'am.

955
01:02:02.071 --> 01:02:05.033
But you ain't seen nothin' yet.
Watch this.

956
01:02:06.701 --> 01:02:11.039
<i>♪ I can be beautiful
Lovely and fair ♪</i>

957
01:02:11.081 --> 01:02:15.293
<i>♪ Silvery voice Long purple hair ♪</i>

958
01:02:15.335 --> 01:02:19.172
<i>♪ La la la-la La la la la-la ♪</i>

959
01:02:19.255 --> 01:02:23.093
<i>♪ La la-la la la
La-la la-la la la ♪</i>

960
01:02:23.176 --> 01:02:27.514
<i>♪ But it's only skin-deep
Zim zabberim zim ♪</i>

961
01:02:27.555 --> 01:02:29.974
<i>♪ I'm an ugly old creep ♪</i>

962
01:02:30.016 --> 01:02:35.355
<i>♪ The magnificent, marvellous,
mad, mad, mad, mad Madam Mim ♪</i>

963
01:02:38.775 --> 01:02:40.860
Now what do you think, boy?

964
01:02:40.902 --> 01:02:43.530
Who's the greatest?

965
01:02:44.114 --> 01:02:47.617
Well, Merlin's magic is always...

966
01:02:47.659 --> 01:02:51.037
well, useful for something good.

967
01:02:51.079 --> 01:02:54.290
And he must see something good in you.

968
01:02:54.332 --> 01:02:55.917
Oh, I suppose so.

969
01:02:55.959 --> 01:02:58.253
Yes, and in my book that's bad.

970
01:02:59.337 --> 01:03:03.758
So, my boy,
I'm afraid I'll have to destroy you.

971
01:03:03.800 --> 01:03:05.927
De... Destroy me?

972
01:03:05.969 --> 01:03:08.596
Yeah, I'll give you a sporting chance.

973
01:03:08.638 --> 01:03:11.307
I'm mad about games, you know.

974
01:03:11.349 --> 01:03:13.643
Well, come on. Get going, boy.

975
01:03:13.685 --> 01:03:16.146
You gotta keep on your toes
in this game.

976
01:03:16.229 --> 01:03:18.648
[cackling]

977
01:03:26.739 --> 01:03:28.700
I win, I win!

978
01:03:28.742 --> 01:03:30.952
Oh, the game's over.

979
01:03:32.203 --> 01:03:33.455
Ah!

980
01:03:33.496 --> 01:03:35.373
Why, you little devil, you!

981
01:03:35.415 --> 01:03:38.042
I'll wring your scrawny little neck.

982
01:03:38.710 --> 01:03:40.336
Mim. Mim!

983
01:03:40.378 --> 01:03:43.047
What...? What are you up to?

984
01:03:43.089 --> 01:03:44.632
Oh, Merlin.

985
01:03:44.674 --> 01:03:48.595
Well, you're just in time.
We were playing a little game.

986
01:03:48.636 --> 01:03:50.930
She was going to destroy me.

987
01:03:50.972 --> 01:03:54.142
And just what are you gonna do about it?

988
01:03:54.184 --> 01:03:57.771
Want to fight?
Want to have a wizards' duel?

989
01:03:59.230 --> 01:04:00.940
As you wish, Madam.

990
01:04:00.982 --> 01:04:03.943
Well, come on. Step outside.

991
01:04:03.985 --> 01:04:06.154
After you, Madam.

992
01:04:18.750 --> 01:04:21.336
What... what's up, boy?
What's going on?

993
01:04:21.377 --> 01:04:24.005
They're having a wizards' duel.
What's that?

994
01:04:24.047 --> 01:04:25.590
Oh, it's a battle of wits.

995
01:04:25.632 --> 01:04:29.219
The players change themselves
to different things

996
01:04:29.260 --> 01:04:33.056
- and attempt to destroy one another.
- De... Destroy?

997
01:04:33.098 --> 01:04:35.266
Just watch, boy.
You'll get the idea.

998
01:04:38.561 --> 01:04:40.730
[muffled] First, if you don't mind,

999
01:04:40.772 --> 01:04:43.817
- I'll make the rules.
- Rules, indeed.

1000
01:04:43.858 --> 01:04:46.319
She only wants rules
so she can break them.

1001
01:04:46.361 --> 01:04:49.656
I'll take care of you later,
featherbrain.

1002
01:04:49.697 --> 01:04:53.076
Rule one, no mineral or vegetable.

1003
01:04:53.118 --> 01:04:54.452
Only animal.

1004
01:04:54.494 --> 01:04:59.457
Rule two, no make-believe things
like, oh... pink dragons and stuff.

1005
01:04:59.958 --> 01:05:02.502
Rule three, no disappearing.

1006
01:05:02.544 --> 01:05:06.005
No. Rule four, no cheating.

1007
01:05:06.047 --> 01:05:08.758
All right, all right.
Now, pace off ten.

1008
01:05:10.260 --> 01:05:13.930
One, two, three, four...

1009
01:05:13.972 --> 01:05:16.891
- Merlin, she disappeared.
- Huh?

1010
01:05:16.933 --> 01:05:19.519
Mim, now, you made the rules.

1011
01:05:23.481 --> 01:05:25.525
[chuckling]

1012
01:05:25.567 --> 01:05:27.944
Ouch! Ooh!

1013
01:05:31.614 --> 01:05:33.616
[cackling]

1014
01:05:33.658 --> 01:05:36.035
[Arthur] Change to something else,
Merlin.

1015
01:05:36.077 --> 01:05:38.455
Yes, yes, yes, yes.
Give me time to think.

1016
01:05:40.039 --> 01:05:42.333
HiggitY figgity... No, no.

1017
01:05:42.375 --> 01:05:44.002
Quick, Merlin, hurry!

1018
01:05:44.043 --> 01:05:46.171
Hoppity WP-

1019
01:05:46.212 --> 01:05:48.131
Aha!

1020
01:05:50.425 --> 01:05:52.302
Madam, just a minute.

1021
01:05:52.343 --> 01:05:54.095
This is not...

1022
01:05:54.137 --> 01:05:58.349
[cackling]

1023
01:05:59.809 --> 01:06:02.520
- Come on, something bigger.
- Something smaller.

1024
01:06:02.562 --> 01:06:04.522
- Mim... M, M... Mim...
- [crash]

1025
01:06:04.564 --> 01:06:06.149
[Mim shouts]

1026
01:06:06.191 --> 01:06:09.778
[Mim laughing]

1027
01:06:09.819 --> 01:06:11.863
[laughter stops]

1028
01:06:11.905 --> 01:06:13.615
Merlin?

1029
01:06:13.656 --> 01:06:16.993
- No disappearing.
- [panting] Whew!

1030
01:06:18.119 --> 01:06:20.497
Oh! Oh, oh!

1031
01:06:24.167 --> 01:06:27.087
[clucking]

1032
01:06:30.757 --> 01:06:32.884
Ouch!

1033
01:06:39.682 --> 01:06:41.226
Mim? Mim?

1034
01:06:41.267 --> 01:06:44.813
Are you...?
What's going on here?

1035
01:06:44.854 --> 01:06:47.232
You... You big blimp.

1036
01:06:49.442 --> 01:06:51.986
[screams]

1037
01:06:54.531 --> 01:06:56.658
[roaring]

1038
01:06:56.699 --> 01:06:58.451
[cackles]

1039
01:06:58.493 --> 01:07:01.037
Squash me, will ya?

1040
01:07:05.166 --> 01:07:08.461
- [rattling]
- Ah, ah, ah, ah, Merlin.

1041
01:07:09.629 --> 01:07:11.339
Ouch! Ooh!

1042
01:07:11.381 --> 01:07:13.216
Bravo.

1043
01:07:15.552 --> 01:07:18.721
Just you wait, just you wait.
You're gonna pay.

1044
01:07:34.612 --> 01:07:38.032
So, you want to play rough, do you?

1045
01:07:40.201 --> 01:07:42.078
All right, Merlin.

1046
01:07:42.120 --> 01:07:45.707
I'll smash you good, you old crab.

1047
01:07:46.708 --> 01:07:48.543
Jehoshaphat.

1048
01:07:50.044 --> 01:07:53.882
Here I come, Mim, ready or not.

1049
01:07:56.050 --> 01:07:57.635
Merlin, you wouldn't dare.

1050
01:07:57.677 --> 01:07:59.804
Merlin!

1051
01:07:59.846 --> 01:08:02.599
[screams]

1052
01:08:09.564 --> 01:08:12.525
[gasps] Now, Mim, Mim,
no dragons, remember?

1053
01:08:12.567 --> 01:08:16.571
Did I say no purple dragons?
Did I?!

1054
01:08:26.456 --> 01:08:27.957
[cries out]

1055
01:08:27.999 --> 01:08:31.044
- [blowing]
- [laughing]

1056
01:08:31.086 --> 01:08:33.546
I win, I win!

1057
01:08:33.588 --> 01:08:37.383
Oh, that horrible old witch.
I'll peck her eyes out.

1058
01:08:37.425 --> 01:08:38.718
No, no.

1059
01:08:41.304 --> 01:08:42.555
[gasps]

1060
01:08:42.597 --> 01:08:45.141
- He's gone.
- Disappeared.

1061
01:08:45.183 --> 01:08:47.727
[Merlin] Madam, I have not disappeared.

1062
01:08:47.769 --> 01:08:49.729
I am very tiny.

1063
01:08:49.771 --> 01:08:52.899
I am a germ, a rare disease.

1064
01:08:52.941 --> 01:08:55.902
I'm called Malagalee Telopterosis.

1065
01:08:55.944 --> 01:08:58.488
And you caught me, Mim.

1066
01:08:58.530 --> 01:09:00.907
- What?!
- [laughing]

1067
01:09:00.949 --> 01:09:03.368
First, you break out into spots.

1068
01:09:06.037 --> 01:09:10.041
Followed by hot and cold flashes.

1069
01:09:10.083 --> 01:09:11.876
[shivering]

1070
01:09:11.918 --> 01:09:14.087
Then violent sneezing.

1071
01:09:14.129 --> 01:09:16.673
Ah... Ah... Ah... Ah...

1072
01:09:16.714 --> 01:09:18.591
Ah-choo!

1073
01:09:18.633 --> 01:09:20.218
Watch it, boy.

1074
01:09:20.343 --> 01:09:22.470
[shouts] Oh! You, you, you...

1075
01:09:22.512 --> 01:09:25.181
You sneaky old scoundrel!

1076
01:09:25.223 --> 01:09:28.893
[crying]

1077
01:09:32.063 --> 01:09:35.900
[Merlin] It's not too serious, Madam.
You should recover in a few weeks

1078
01:09:35.984 --> 01:09:39.571
and be as good...
I mean, as bad, as ever.

1079
01:09:39.654 --> 01:09:42.115
But I would suggest plenty of rest

1080
01:09:42.198 --> 01:09:46.202
and lots and lots of sunshine.

1081
01:09:47.120 --> 01:09:49.497
I hate sunshine.

1082
01:09:49.539 --> 01:09:53.334
I hate horrible wholesome sunshine!

1083
01:09:53.376 --> 01:09:55.462
I hate it, I hate it!

1084
01:09:55.503 --> 01:09:58.089
I hate, hate, hate...

1085
01:09:58.131 --> 01:10:02.177
You were really great, Merlin.
But you could have been killed.

1086
01:10:02.218 --> 01:10:05.430
It was worth it, lad,
if you learned something from it.

1087
01:10:06.639 --> 01:10:09.058
Knowledge and wisdom is the real power.

1088
01:10:09.100 --> 01:10:12.771
Right you are, Wart.
So, stick to your schooling, boy.

1089
01:10:12.812 --> 01:10:15.565
Oh, don't worry.
I will, sir. I will.

1090
01:10:15.607 --> 01:10:17.025
Oh, I really will.

1091
01:10:18.902 --> 01:10:22.655
[Men] I We will sing
all night and all day

1092
01:10:22.697 --> 01:10:27.786
<i>♪ We will fight for the blue oak tree
On a field of white ♪</i>

1093
01:10:27.827 --> 01:10:29.871
<i>♪ For the blue oak tree ♪</i>

1094
01:10:29.913 --> 01:10:35.335
<i>♪ On a field of white ♪</i>

1095
01:10:37.337 --> 01:10:40.757
[men laughing]

1096
01:10:40.799 --> 01:10:44.969
Here's to victory in London
for my son, Kay.

1097
01:10:45.011 --> 01:10:48.431
Sir Kay.
I've been knighted, don't forget.

1098
01:10:48.473 --> 01:10:51.684
Oh, of course, son, of course.

1099
01:10:51.726 --> 01:10:54.395
Here's to Sir Kay.

1100
01:10:54.437 --> 01:10:58.274
And who knows?
The future king of all England.

1101
01:10:58.358 --> 01:10:59.984
Watch it, will ya?

1102
01:11:00.026 --> 01:11:02.070
Kay the king?

1103
01:11:02.112 --> 01:11:04.656
What a dreadful thought.

1104
01:11:04.697 --> 01:11:08.785
Sir Ector, Sir Ector,
Hobbs has come down with the mumps.

1105
01:11:09.452 --> 01:11:13.039
He's all puffed up like a toad.

1106
01:11:13.123 --> 01:11:16.584
Then Kay will need another squire,
hang it all.

1107
01:11:16.626 --> 01:11:19.504
- Wart, you're it.
- I'm what, sir?

1108
01:11:19.546 --> 01:11:21.923
Kay's squire.
You're going to London.

1109
01:11:21.965 --> 01:11:24.676
Oh, Sir Ector!
Wha...? Wait. Whoa!

1110
01:11:28.138 --> 01:11:31.307
Merlin, Archimedes, Merlin!

1111
01:11:33.810 --> 01:11:36.771
Merlin, look! I'm a squire.

1112
01:11:36.813 --> 01:11:38.606
Ha!

1113
01:11:39.732 --> 01:11:43.069
Oh. Very nice, boy.

1114
01:11:43.820 --> 01:11:45.739
Yes, indeed.

1115
01:11:45.780 --> 01:11:49.701
A fine monkey suit for polishing boots.

1116
01:11:49.743 --> 01:11:51.703
It's what all squires wear.

1117
01:11:51.745 --> 01:11:55.290
And I thought you were going
to amount to something.

1118
01:11:55.331 --> 01:11:57.917
I thought you had a few brains!

1119
01:11:59.252 --> 01:12:01.921
Great future. Ha!

1120
01:12:01.963 --> 01:12:05.800
A stooge for that love you, Kay.

1121
01:12:05.842 --> 01:12:08.428
Congratulations, boy!

1122
01:12:09.262 --> 01:12:11.139
What do you want me to be?

1123
01:12:11.181 --> 01:12:13.057
I'm nobody. You...

1124
01:12:13.099 --> 01:12:16.394
You don't know a thing
about what's going on today.

1125
01:12:16.436 --> 01:12:18.730
I'm lucky to be Kay's squire.

1126
01:12:18.813 --> 01:12:22.567
Oh! Of all the idiotic...

1127
01:12:22.609 --> 01:12:24.152
[stammering] I...

1128
01:12:24.194 --> 01:12:26.404
Blow me to Bermuda!

1129
01:12:34.621 --> 01:12:38.208
- Where did he go?
- To Bermuda, I suppose.

1130
01:12:38.291 --> 01:12:41.377
- Where's that?
- Oh, an island way off somewhere

1131
01:12:41.419 --> 01:12:45.256
- that hasn't been discovered yet.
- Will he ever come back?

1132
01:12:45.340 --> 01:12:48.176
Who knows? Who knows anything?

1133
01:12:53.139 --> 01:12:56.059
[man] For the crown of all England,

1134
01:12:56.101 --> 01:12:58.645
let the tournament begin!

1135
01:12:58.686 --> 01:13:02.524
- [whinnying]
- [crowd cheering]

1136
01:13:17.372 --> 01:13:20.792
Kay! Now, it's up to the swords.

1137
01:13:20.834 --> 01:13:23.294
Swords? Swords?!

1138
01:13:23.378 --> 01:13:24.838
Oh, no!

1139
01:13:24.879 --> 01:13:27.424
- Kay.
- What? What?

1140
01:13:27.465 --> 01:13:30.927
I... I forgot your sword.

1141
01:13:30.969 --> 01:13:33.596
Forgot my sword!

1142
01:13:33.638 --> 01:13:36.474
I... I left it back at the inn.

1143
01:13:36.516 --> 01:13:40.645
Why, you bungling little fool!

1144
01:13:40.687 --> 01:13:44.190
You'd better get it,
or don't you dare come back!

1145
01:13:49.279 --> 01:13:51.072
Let me in, let me in!

1146
01:13:51.990 --> 01:13:54.659
Somebody, please!
Please let me in!

1147
01:13:54.701 --> 01:13:57.829
It's no use, boy,
they've all gone to the tournament.

1148
01:13:57.871 --> 01:14:01.791
Oh, what will I do?
Kay's got to have a sword.

1149
01:14:01.833 --> 01:14:04.669
Look, boy. Look.
There in the churchyard.

1150
01:14:04.711 --> 01:14:07.881
A sword.
Oh, Archimedes. A sword!

1151
01:14:10.216 --> 01:14:13.803
[Archimedes] You're gonna have
a time pulling it out.

1152
01:14:13.887 --> 01:14:15.388
Watch it, boy.

1153
01:14:23.563 --> 01:14:25.190
Better leave it alone.

1154
01:14:25.231 --> 01:14:28.735
But Kay's got to have a sword.

1155
01:14:31.029 --> 01:14:33.698
Now, come on, quick.
Let's get out of here.

1156
01:14:36.201 --> 01:14:39.204
You're up next, son.
Better get ready.

1157
01:14:39.245 --> 01:14:41.456
[Arthur] Kay, Kay, here's a sword.

1158
01:14:42.957 --> 01:14:46.795
- This is not my sword.
- Hold on, Kay.

1159
01:14:46.878 --> 01:14:48.129
Wait a minute.

1160
01:14:48.171 --> 01:14:51.382
"Whoso pulleth out this sword..."

1161
01:14:53.051 --> 01:14:55.595
It's the sword in the stone.

1162
01:14:55.637 --> 01:14:58.681
The sword in the stone?
It can't be.

1163
01:14:58.723 --> 01:15:00.266
But look, it is.

1164
01:15:00.308 --> 01:15:03.603
- It's the marvellous sword.
- Hold everything.

1165
01:15:03.645 --> 01:15:07.398
Someone's pulled the sword
from the stone!

1166
01:15:07.440 --> 01:15:10.068
Where did you get it, Wart?

1167
01:15:10.110 --> 01:15:13.947
I pulled it out of an anvil
that was on a stone

1168
01:15:13.988 --> 01:15:16.032
in... in a churchyard.

1169
01:15:16.074 --> 01:15:19.035
[all laughing]

1170
01:15:19.077 --> 01:15:21.788
The lad's a young Samson.

1171
01:15:21.830 --> 01:15:24.541
You're making a fool of us, boy.

1172
01:15:24.582 --> 01:15:27.710
- Now, tell the truth.
- But I did, sir.

1173
01:15:27.752 --> 01:15:30.797
Then come on. Prove it.
To the stone with you.

1174
01:15:31.840 --> 01:15:33.216
[man] Yes, prove it.

1175
01:15:33.258 --> 01:15:33.800
[man] Yes, prove it.

1176
01:15:33.842 --> 01:15:36.052
[man 2] Come on! Prove it!

1177
01:15:42.225 --> 01:15:46.146
All right, boy, let's have the miracle.

1178
01:15:51.025 --> 01:15:52.902
Now, wait a minute.

1179
01:15:52.944 --> 01:15:56.614
Anyone can pull it
once it's been pulled.

1180
01:15:58.491 --> 01:16:01.786
Go to it, Kay.
Give it all you've got.

1181
01:16:01.828 --> 01:16:05.665
- Put your back into it.
- [men clamouring]

1182
01:16:05.749 --> 01:16:08.042
- Get out.
- Push him aside.

1183
01:16:09.335 --> 01:16:13.298
- There's four. That's not fair.
- I say we let the boy try it.

1184
01:16:13.339 --> 01:16:16.760
That's what I say.
Give the boy a chance.

1185
01:16:16.801 --> 01:16:18.636
Go ahead, son.

1186
01:16:31.649 --> 01:16:35.070
It's a miracle,
ordained by heaven.

1187
01:16:35.111 --> 01:16:37.572
This boy is our king.

1188
01:16:37.614 --> 01:16:40.700
Well, by Jove.

1189
01:16:40.742 --> 01:16:43.870
- [man] What's the lad's name?
- Wart.

1190
01:16:43.912 --> 01:16:45.580
Oh, I mean, Arthur.

1191
01:16:45.622 --> 01:16:47.916
[man] Hail, King Arthur!

1192
01:16:47.957 --> 01:16:51.669
[all] Hail, King Arthur!
Long live the king!

1193
01:16:51.711 --> 01:16:54.964
[laughs] I can't believe it.

1194
01:16:55.006 --> 01:16:58.093
Oh, forgive me, son.

1195
01:16:59.344 --> 01:17:02.305
- Forgive me.
- Oh, please don't, sir.

1196
01:17:02.347 --> 01:17:05.475
Kay, bow down to your king.

1197
01:17:12.107 --> 01:17:15.193
[Narrator] So, at last,
a miracle had come to pass

1198
01:17:15.235 --> 01:17:18.279
in that far-off time
upon New Year's Day.

1199
01:17:18.321 --> 01:17:22.700
And the glorious reign
of King Arthur was begun.

1200
01:17:22.742 --> 01:17:24.369
[sighs]

1201
01:17:26.329 --> 01:17:28.289
I can't be a king, Archimedes.

1202
01:17:28.331 --> 01:17:30.917
I don't know anything
about ruling a country.

1203
01:17:30.959 --> 01:17:34.671
I told you to leave the thing
in the stone, boy.

1204
01:17:34.712 --> 01:17:37.715
I'll run away, that's what I'll do.

1205
01:17:40.885 --> 01:17:44.431
- They'll have to get somebody else.
- Better take the side door.

1206
01:17:44.472 --> 01:17:46.766
Out the side door.

1207
01:17:50.270 --> 01:17:53.731
[crowd] Hail, King Arthur!
Long live the king!

1208
01:17:55.900 --> 01:17:59.571
There's another door over there.
Over there, come on. Come on.

1209
01:18:02.949 --> 01:18:05.034
[crowd] Long live King Arthur!

1210
01:18:05.076 --> 01:18:06.953
Long live...

1211
01:18:08.288 --> 01:18:10.248
Looks like we're surrounded, boy.

1212
01:18:10.290 --> 01:18:14.043
Oh, Archimedes, I wish Merlin was here.

1213
01:18:16.713 --> 01:18:19.382
Merlin! Merlin!

1214
01:18:24.137 --> 01:18:26.514
Oh, Merlin, you're back
from Ber... Ber...

1215
01:18:26.556 --> 01:18:28.391
Bermuda? Yes.

1216
01:18:28.433 --> 01:18:32.020
Back from Bermuda and the 20th century.

1217
01:18:33.104 --> 01:18:36.107
And believe me, you can have it.

1218
01:18:36.149 --> 01:18:39.569
One big modern mess.

1219
01:18:39.611 --> 01:18:41.738
Alakazam.

1220
01:18:41.780 --> 01:18:46.076
- I'm in an awful pickle. I'm king.
- He pulled the sword from the stone.

1221
01:18:46.117 --> 01:18:47.744
Ha ha!

1222
01:18:47.786 --> 01:18:49.704
Of course, of course.

1223
01:18:49.746 --> 01:18:53.792
King Arthur
and his Knights of the Round Table.

1224
01:18:53.833 --> 01:18:57.545
- "Round Table"?
- Would you rather have a square one?

1225
01:18:57.587 --> 01:18:59.881
Oh, no. Round will be fine.

1226
01:18:59.923 --> 01:19:01.508
[chuckles]

1227
01:19:01.549 --> 01:19:03.718
Boy, boy, boy.

1228
01:19:03.760 --> 01:19:06.304
You'll become a great legend.

1229
01:19:06.346 --> 01:19:09.682
